RACE.RACE_TEXT: PLEASANTON RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 76. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUALITY CAT settled just off of the early pace and raced widest into the backstretch run, tracked outside of rivals to the far turn, was roused four wide nearing the quarter marker, vied for the lead into upper stretch and took a narrow advantage to the furlong marker, held WAY TOO HOT at bay while battling that rival inside of the furlong pole, drifted in under firm urging into deep stretch, shook free in the final stages and held in a drive at the finish to prevail. WAY TOO HOT stalked the moderate pace while outside of rivals, prompted the pace through the backstretch run, was roused three wide nearing the quarter marker, vied for the lead between runners into upper stretch, fought back to the furlong grounds while inside of QUALITY CAT, drifted out under left-handed urging in the drive while battling QUALITY CAT, was bumped and crowded by that rival heading to the sixteenth-marker, could not match strides with the winner in deep stretch and was outfinished, while besting the rest. MOVIETIME stalked the moderate pace while inside of rivals, could not keep pace in the drive and weakened in deep stretch, while holding clearly for third. TRIBUTE TO M hesitated at the start and was off slowly, settled outside of runners into the backstretch run, was coaxed along two wide into the far turn and did not offer a response in the stretch. CHELSIESDANZIGLITE broke alertly and dictated terms in the early stages, set modest fractions to the far turn, was overtaken leaving the quarter marker and gave way in the drive. FRESNO CHILE chased inside of rivals along the first turn, was steered four into the four path along the far turn and tired. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INTO THE STRETCH RUN. IN A UNANIMOUS DECISION, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT THERE WAS MUTUAL DRIFTING BETWEEN QUALITY CAT AND WAY TOO HOT AND THAT THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

ENTRY.NAME: Chelsiesdanziglite
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke alertly,set pace,caught upper,gave way stretch

BROOKYS GAL chased the decent early pace, advanced three wide on the turn, was no match for the winner in the stretch drive and ran on to be best of the rest. BIG CATTY showed early speed and pressed the pace while inside of a rival, chased VINOS ANGEL along the turn, weakened in the stretch, was outfinished for second and was clear for third at the finish. CEE'S THE IMAGE lacked early speed, was coaxed along in the three path to the quarter marker and did not threaten. CATTIN ALL AROUND ducked in at the start and was away slowly, chased inside of rivals on the turn, was steered three wide into the drive and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAGAZINE broke alertly and dictated terms in the early stages, set moderate fractions while prompted into the far turn, shook free into upper stretch and drew clear nearing the furlong marker, was kept to task under firm urging to the sixteenth-marker and was geared down in deep stretch to be much the best. ADAPTED MEMORY tracked the pacesetter into the first turn then advanced along the backstretch run and prompted the moderate pace into the second turn, kept close attendance to MAGAZINE to the quarter marker, lost ground into upper stretch, was no match for the winner in the final furlong and outfinished GIANT KID in deep stretch to be best of the rest. GIANT KID took back off of the decent early pace and saved ground into the first turn, stalked the moderate pace through the backstretch run, came within aim while two wide nearing the quarter marker, chased MAGAZINE to mid-stretch, tired in the final sixteenth and was outfinished for second, while clear in the end for third. RAFANELLI broke out a bit leaving the start, settled in the second flight in the early stages, raced between rivals along the backstretch run, was shuffled back nearing the half-mile marker, chased along the far turn, could not keep pace into the stretch and gave way. GRASPY settled just off of the early pace while inside of rivals, tracked the pace to the half-mile marker and dropped back along the second turn.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOB BOSS broke alertly and was sent to the early lead, disputed the pace while inside of a rival heading to the turn, set moderate fractions while pressed to the quarter marker, held a narrow lead into upper stretch, was confronted at the furlong pole by WICKLOW HILLS, dueled with that foe into deep stretch, dug in in the final sixteenth and determinedly held the runner-up at bay in the final strides to prevail. WICKLOW HILLS was brushed at the start by a neighboring rival and was off a step slowly, recovered to chase the moderate early pace from mid-pack while outside of runners, made a steady advance to the quarter marker while widest, was asked for run five wide into upper stretch, rallied and confronted MOB BOSS at the furlong marker, drew to even terms with that foe into deep stretch, was denied the win by the determined MOB BOSS in the final strides and held safely at the finish for second. RACE.RACE_TEXT: PLEASANTON RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 71. Maiden Claiming Purse 12500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TWICE FOOLED was allowed to settle into stride, took an inside path, moved into contention through the turn, waited for an opening along the inside turning for home then surged through when the rail opened up and outran the field to the wire from there. MOTOWN CLASSIC veered out at the start and bothered SON OF SHANGHAI just after the break, raced forwardly tracking the dueling leaders to the turn, was set down to go after the lead with about three furlongs to run, had a head in front at the top of the stretch then could not match strides with the winner but was well clear of the third horse. START THEM UP was in tight quarters after the break and fell back to last in the early going, lagged near the rear of the field to the stretch then made a big late rally to gain third. ONE LITTLE INDIAN was slowly into stride and spotted the field a few lengths early, angled towards the rail before the turn, showed a little late run down the stretch while never a serious threat. VIVA LEON JODIDO bothered a bit from the inside but was asked to set out for the early lead, sat just to the outside of TACOMA SOUND and dueled with that rival through the turn, made a bid to take command at the head of the stretch but was spent from the early efforts and came up empty for the stretch run. TACOMA SOUND broke out at the start and brushed VIVA LEON JODIDO, was sent for and gained the early lead with that foe a neck behind to the outside, battled to the top of the stretch then was overtaken for the inside and outside and gave way readily. WAKES AND WEDDINGS settled in mid-pack for the first quarter mile, moved into contention through the turn, came into the stretch five wide but could not muster a rally. SON OF SHANGHAI squeezed at the start then almost immediately came under a ride, only had one beat down the backstretch, started to make some forward progress through the turn while still being ridden then tired under pressure in mid-stretch. RIVER'S BENCHMARK stumbled slightly at the break, raced mid-pack for the first half mile but was caught five wide, made a mild move on the turn and turned into the stretch still five wide then tired before the furlong pole.
